<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <%- include("partials/header") %>
  <body
    style="background-image: linear-gradient(to top, #fbc2eb 0%, #a6c1ee 100%)"
  >
    <%- include("partials/nav") %> <% if (user) { %>
      <div id="home">
        <div>
          <h2 class="title"><%= event.title %></h2>
          <p class="copy"><%= event.date %> | <%= event.time %></p>
          <p class="copy"><%= event.location %></p>
          <p class="copy">₹ <%= event.pricing %></p>
          <% var a= 0; for (let i = 0; i < data.Register.length; i++) { %>
            <%  if(data.Register[i].UID == user.id && data.Register[i].UEID == event.UEID){ %>
          <p ><strong>Registered  <span style="color:#34b233;">&check;</span></strong></p>
              <% a=1; break; %>
              <% } %>
  
  
            <% } %>
          <%  if(a==0){ %>
  
            <div class="button"> <a href="/register/<%= event.UEID %>">Register</a></div>             <% } %>
  
        </div>
        <div>
          <img src="<%= event.poster %>" alt="" />
        </div>
      </div>
  
      <div class="description">
        <h2>Description</h2>
        <p class="copy"><%= event.description %></p>
      </div>
      <div class="terms">
        <h2>Terms and Conditions</h2>
        <p><strong>1. Registration and Attendance:</strong></p>
        <p>
          a. Participants must register for the event using the provided
          registration process.
        </p>
        <p>
          b. Attendance at the event is subject to availability and may require
          confirmation or approval.
        </p>
        <p>
          c. The event organizer reserves the right to refuse or cancel
          registrations or attendance at their discretion.
        </p>
  
        <p><strong>2. Event Content and Changes:</strong></p>
        <p>
          a. The event program, schedule, speakers, and content are subject to
          change without prior notice.
        </p>
        <p>
          b. The event organizer will make reasonable efforts to provide accurate
          and up-to-date information regarding the event.
        </p>
  
        <p><strong>3. Payment and Refunds:</strong></p>
        <p>
          a. Payment for event registration must be made in full at the time of
          registration.
        </p>
        <p>
          b. Refunds for event registration fees may be available based on the
          organizer's refund policy, which will be communicated to participants.
        </p>
  
        <p><strong>4. Cancellation and Postponement:</strong></p>
        <p>
          a. The event organizer reserves the right to cancel or postpone the
          event due to unforeseen circumstances, including but not limited to
          natural disasters, public health emergencies, or other factors beyond
          their control.
        </p>
        <p>
          b. In the event of cancellation or postponement, the organizer will make
          reasonable efforts to provide information on rescheduling, refunds, or
          alternative arrangements.
        </p>
  
        <p><strong>5. Code of Conduct:</strong></p>
        <p>
          a. Participants are expected to conduct themselves in a respectful and
          professional manner during the event.
        </p>
        <p>
          b. Harassment, discrimination, or any form of disruptive behavior will
          not be tolerated and may result in removal from the event without
          refund.
        </p>
  
        <p><strong>6. Liability and Disclaimer:</strong></p>
        <p>
          a. The event organizer and its affiliates shall not be held liable for
          any loss, damage, injury, or inconvenience incurred during the event.
        </p>
        <p>
          b. Participants are responsible for their personal belongings, safety,
          and well-being during the event.
        </p>
  
        <p><strong>7. Intellectual Property:</strong></p>
        <p>
          a. All intellectual property rights, including but not limited to event
          materials, presentations, and recordings, are owned by the event
          organizer or the respective rights holders.
        </p>
        <p>
          b. Participants shall not reproduce, distribute, modify, or use any
          event materials without prior written consent from the event organizer.
        </p>
  
        <p><strong>8. Privacy and Data Protection:</strong></p>
        <p>
          a. The event organizer may collect and process personal information
          provided by participants for event registration and related purposes.
        </p>
        <p>
          b. Participant data will be handled in accordance with applicable
          privacy laws and the event organizer's privacy policy.
        </p>
  
        <p><strong>9. Photography and Media:</strong></p>
        <p>
          a. By attending the event, participants grant the event organizer the
          right to capture and use photographs, videos, or other media taken
          during the event for promotional purposes.
        </p>
  
        <p><strong>10. Indemnity:</strong></p>
        <p>
          a. Participants agree to indemnify and hold harmless the event
          organizer, its affiliates, and partners from any claims, damages, or
          liabilities arising from their participation in the event.
        </p>
  
        <p><strong>11. Governing Law and Jurisdiction:</strong></p>
        <p>
          a. These terms and conditions shall be governed by and construed in
          accordance with the laws of India.
        </p>
        <p>
          b. Any disputes arising from these terms and conditions shall be subject
          to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts in India.
        </p>
  
        <p><strong>12. Severability:</strong></p>
        <p>
          a. If any provision of these terms and conditions is deemed invalid or
          unenforceable, the remaining provisions shall remain in full force and
          effect.
        </p>
      </div>
      <% } else { %>
      <div id="home">
        <div>
          <h2 class="title">Access Denied</h2>
          <p class="copy">
            You Need To Login First to Access the Event Registration Page
          </p>
          <div class="button">
            <a href="/auth/google">Login</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <img src="/Images/error.svg" alt="" />
        </div>
      </div>
      <% } %>  
      <%- include("partials/footer") %>
  </body>
</html>
